    <!-- Overview Section -->
    <section>
        <h2 class="section-title">Overview</h2>
        <p>
            The Arroceros Forest Park, often called the “Last Lung of Manila,” is a lush green oasis located along Antonio Villegas Street near the Pasig River.
            This urban forest spans around 2.2 hectares and is home to more than 60 species of trees and over 8,000 ornamental plants.
            It serves as a peaceful escape amid the bustling city and provides an important habitat for birds and other wildlife.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Free Entrance</strong></p>
    </section>

    <!-- Highlights Section -->
    <section>
        <h3 class="section-title">Highlights</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Known as the “Last Lung of Manila” for its dense forest cover.</li>
            <li>Over 60 species of trees and thousands of ornamental plants.</li>
            <li>Features walking paths, gazebos, and open green spaces.</li>
            <li>Ideal for nature lovers, photographers, and families seeking peace in the city.</li>
            <li>Managed with the help of environmental advocates and local volunteers.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Location Section -->
